'''Arborsculpture''' is a branch of [[Arboriculture]] specifically involved with the shaping of trees into structures useful to man. Naturally occuring arborsculptural events, although not always useful to man but often noteworthy - are termed [[Inosculation]]. The art of arborsculpture as practiced in living branches is called [[pleaching]].
The term Arborsculpture was coined in the 1990's but the practice can be dated back thousands of years.